Defendant Kimberly A Shannon in court with attorney Vincent P Guimont.  James C Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Statements made as to sentencing.
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 months in the House of Correction, each count, consecutive to each other and consecutive to any other time, with credit for 0 DAYS time served.  This sentence is STAYED and defendant placed on PROBATION for a period of 2 years, each count concurrent with the following conditions:
-Cooperate with the Department
-Cooperate with any treatment deemed appropriate
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause

-Seek / Maintain full time employment
-Pay restitution of $2,500 to Aldridge Inc-to be paid out first- and $14,362 to Society Insurance over period of probation.  Upon successful completion or revocation, any balance remaining unpaid is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant
No contact with any George Webbs in Milwaukee County
The Court ordered the defendant to pay applicable costs, surcharges and assessments over period of probation.  Upon successful completion or revocation, any balance remaining unpaid is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant

Upon revocation should not be served on electronic monitoring.

The Court ordered the defendant to provide a DNA sample, surcharge waived in the interest of paying restitution. 
Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  kmw
